<emphasis box="[827,959,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">Coloration:</emphasis>
Head, mesosoma, fore and midlegs dark brown. 
<collectingCountry box="[236,292,223,248]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">Hind</collectingCountry>
leg and metasoma brown (
<figureCitation box="[595,663,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,375,1508]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,375,1521]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Centris ferruginea Lepeletier, 1841. Fig. 5. Female (Amazonas: Puerto Santander): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 6. Habitus, lateral view (scale bar 5 mm). Fig. 7. Male (Amazonas: Leticia): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 8. Habitus, lateral view (Scale bar 5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284324/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
Fig. 
<number box="[647,663,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Clypeus with two rhomboid yellow spots (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1228,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,375,1508]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,375,1521]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Centris ferruginea Lepeletier, 1841. Fig. 5. Female (Amazonas: Puerto Santander): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 6. Habitus, lateral view (scale bar 5 mm). Fig. 7. Male (Amazonas: Leticia): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 8. Habitus, lateral view (Scale bar 5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284324/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
Fig. 
<number box="[1212,1228,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wing membrane dark brown. 
<emphasis box="[292,408,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">Sculpture:</emphasis>
Clypeus coriaceus with disc relatively thick and with dispersed punctation at sides. Labrum with fine and dense punctation; basal margin with a smooth area. Mesoscutum and mesoscutellum with fine, dense and relatively uniform punctation. 
<emphasis box="[554,695,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">Pubescence:</emphasis>
White yellowish on gena, paraocular and malar areas, between ocelli and on the base of the mandible (
<figureCitation box="[604,674,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,375,1508]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,375,1521]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Centris ferruginea Lepeletier, 1841. Fig. 5. Female (Amazonas: Puerto Santander): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 6. Habitus, lateral view (scale bar 5 mm). Fig. 7. Male (Amazonas: Leticia): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 8. Habitus, lateral view (Scale bar 5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284324/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
Fig. 
<number box="[658,674,367,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Vertex and interantenal area with dark brown hairs. Supraclypeal area with dark brown and white yellowish hairs mixed. Labrum with light yellow hairs. Mesoscutum, tegula and mesoscutellum with brown hairs. Laterodorsal area of the pronotum, anterior area of pronotal lobe, axilla and posterior surface of the mesoscutellum with yellow hairs (
<figureCitation box="[801,869,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,375,1508]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,375,1521]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Centris ferruginea Lepeletier, 1841. Fig. 5. Female (Amazonas: Puerto Santander): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 6. Habitus, lateral view (scale bar 5 mm). Fig. 7. Male (Amazonas: Leticia): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 8. Habitus, lateral view (Scale bar 5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284324/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
Fig. 
<number box="[853,869,476,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Mesepisternum with brown pilosity, light yellow on the rest of the mesosoma. Tarsi of fore and midlegs with orange hairs. Fore femur and tibia with white yellowish hairs. Middle tibia with dark brown pilosity. 
<collectingCountry box="[657,713,548,573]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">Hind</collectingCountry>
leg with yellow hairs. T 
<number box="[993,1003,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" value="1.0">1</number>
with white yellowish hairs, orange on the other terga. Sterna with yellowish hairs. Prepygidial and pygidial fimbriae yellow. 
<emphasis box="[1139,1261,584,607]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">Structures:</emphasis>
Mandible with four teeth, along the fifth on the inner surface. First, second and fourth tooth with narrowly rounded apex. Third tooth with relatively straight apex (
<figureCitation box="[552,622,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,375,1508]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,375,1521]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Centris ferruginea Lepeletier, 1841. Fig. 5. Female (Amazonas: Puerto Santander): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 6. Habitus, lateral view (scale bar 5 mm). Fig. 7. Male (Amazonas: Leticia): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 8. Habitus, lateral view (Scale bar 5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284324/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
Fig. 
<number box="[606,622,655,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Trimmal angle acute. Acetabular carina reaching the base of the third tooth. Labrum semicircular. Clypeal disc slightly concave (lateral view). Inner orbits of compound eyes slightly converging below. Vertex above the upper ocular tangent. Secondary anterior comb of fore elaiospathe formed by three hairs. Primary basitibial plate relatively elliptical, secondary plate relatively rhomboid, well developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
