<emphasis box="[763,894,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">Coloration:</emphasis>
Head and mesosoma dark brown. Legs brown. Clypeus predominantly yellow, with brown lateral edge. Labrum yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1007,1079,943,968]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,375,1508]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,375,1521]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Centris ferruginea Lepeletier, 1841. Fig. 5. Female (Amazonas: Puerto Santander): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 6. Habitus, lateral view (scale bar 5 mm). Fig. 7. Male (Amazonas: Leticia): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 8. Habitus, lateral view (Scale bar 5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284324/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
Fig. 
<number box="[1063,1079,944,968]" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wing membrane dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[159,230,980,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,375,1508]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,375,1521]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Centris ferruginea Lepeletier, 1841. Fig. 5. Female (Amazonas: Puerto Santander): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 6. Habitus, lateral view (scale bar 5 mm). Fig. 7. Male (Amazonas: Leticia): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 8. Habitus, lateral view (Scale bar 5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284324/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,230,980,1004]" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[254,369,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">Sculpture:</emphasis>
Clypeus coriaceus with sparse punctures. Clypeal disc unpunctated. Labrum coriaceus, with relatively fine and sparse punctation. Mesoscutum with fine and very dense punctation. 
<emphasis box="[1140,1281,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">Pubescence:</emphasis>
Yellowish on gena, paraocular and malar areas, between ocelli and on the base of the mandible. Vertex and inter-antenal area with dark brown hairs. Supraclypeal area with dark brown and white yellowish hairs mixed. Lateral area of the clypeus with brown and long hairs. Labrum with light yellow hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1031,1110,1124,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,375,1508]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,375,1521]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Centris ferruginea Lepeletier, 1841. Fig. 5. Female (Amazonas: Puerto Santander): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 6. Habitus, lateral view (scale bar 5 mm). Fig. 7. Male (Amazonas: Leticia): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 8. Habitus, lateral view (Scale bar 5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284324/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
Fig. 
<number box="[1094,1110,1124,1148]" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum, tegula and mesoscutellum with brown hairs, darker toward the pronotal lobe. Laterodorsal area of pronotum, pronotal lobe and posterior surface of mesoscutellum with intense yellow hairs. Mesepisternum with light brown hairs, light yellow on the rest of the mesosoma (
<figureCitation box="[582,652,1231,1256]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,375,1508]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,375,1521]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Centris ferruginea Lepeletier, 1841. Fig. 5. Female (Amazonas: Puerto Santander): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 6. Habitus, lateral view (scale bar 5 mm). Fig. 7. Male (Amazonas: Leticia): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 8. Habitus, lateral view (Scale bar 5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284324/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
Fig. 
<number box="[637,652,1232,1256]" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Legs with dark brown hairs, lighter on fore leg, and yellowish on coxae and trochanters. Tarsi of fore and midlegs with orange hairs. Metasoma with orange hairs, except T 
<number box="[1367,1377,1268,1292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" value="1.0">1</number>
with brown pubescence. Claws of middle and hind legs with a tuft of long and plumose hairs at the base. 
<emphasis box="[1313,1435,1304,1327]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">Structures:</emphasis>
Mandible with three teeth of acute apex (
<figureCitation box="[614,683,1340,1365]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,375,1508]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,375,1521]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Centris ferruginea Lepeletier, 1841. Fig. 5. Female (Amazonas: Puerto Santander): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 6. Habitus, lateral view (scale bar 5 mm). Fig. 7. Male (Amazonas: Leticia): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 8. Habitus, lateral view (Scale bar 5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284324/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
Fig. 
<number box="[667,683,1340,1364]" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Trimmal angle obtuse, almost absent. Acetabular carina reaching the base of the third tooth. Clypeal disc slightly concave (lateral view). Labrum semicircular. Inner orbits of compound eyes converging above (
<figureCitation box="[554,624,1412,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,375,1508]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,375,1521]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Centris ferruginea Lepeletier, 1841. Fig. 5. Female (Amazonas: Puerto Santander): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 6. Habitus, lateral view (scale bar 5 mm). Fig. 7. Male (Amazonas: Leticia): Head, frontal view (scale bar 1 mm). Fig. 8. Habitus, lateral view (Scale bar 5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284324/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
Fig. 
<number box="[608,624,1412,1436]" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Distance between the lateral ocellus and the eye approximately twice the diameter of the median ocellus. 
<collectingCountry box="[551,607,1447,1472]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur well developed. Pygidial plate absent.
</paragraph>
